Usage: create_virtual_fin_bound_marker [-help]
                                       [-areas {{lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1} {lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2}...}]
                                       [-drc_region_layer <layer>]
                                       -marker_layer <string> {[-layer <layer> [-net <net>] ] | -inst <inst> | -cell <libCell/ptnCell>}

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-areas {{lx1 ly1 ux1 uy1} {lx2 ly2 ux2 uy2}...}
                              # Specifies the areas to find the marker shapes. (box_list, optional)
-cell <libCell/ptnCell>       # Specifies the cell name.
                              # ((libCell/ptnCell), optional)
-drc_region_layer <layer>     # Add the marker shapes on the objects which
                              # touched drc region. ((layer), optional)
-inst <inst>                  # Specifies the instance name. ((inst), optional)
-layer <layer>                # Specifies the layer name. ((layer), optional)
-marker_layer <string>        # Specifies the customer layer name to put the
                              # marker shapes. (string, required)
-net <net>                    # Specifies the net name. ((net), optional)